## Implementation Plan

### Security Vulnerabilities Addressed

| Alert | Package | Vulnerability | Severity | CVE |
|-------|---------|--------------|----------|-----|
| #102 | @isaacs/brace-expansion | DoS via unbounded brace range expansion | HIGH | CVE-2026-25547 |
| #101 | fast-xml-parser | RangeError DoS via numeric entities | HIGH | CVE-2026-25128 |

### Root Cause Analysis

1. **@isaacs/brace-expansion@5.0.0** - Transitive dependency via:
   - glob@^11.0.0 → minimatch@10.1.1 → @isaacs/brace-expansion@5.0.0
   - @types/rimraf → @types/glob → glob → minimatch → @isaacs/brace-expansion

2. **fast-xml-parser@5.2.5** - Transitive dependency via:
   - @aws-sdk/client-lambda → @aws-sdk/core → @aws-sdk/xml-builder → fast-xml-parser

### Remediation Steps

1. Added pnpm overrides to force patched versions:
   - @isaacs/brace-expansion: ^5.0.1
   - fast-xml-parser: ^5.3.4

2. Updated @aws-sdk/client-lambda from ^3.723.0 to ^3.984.0

3. Verified fixes with pnpm why commands

4. All 806 tests pass, build successful
